  <heading>BFCVTNT</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Single-precision down convert and narrow to BFloat16 (top, predicated)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>Convert to BFloat16 from single-precision in each active floating-point
element of the source vector, and place the results in the
odd-numbered 16-bit elements of the destination vector,
leaving the even-numbered elements unchanged. 
Inactive elements in the destination vector register remain unmodified or
are set to zero, depending on whether merging or zeroing
predication is selected.</para>
      <para>ID_AA64ZFR0_EL1.BF16 indicates whether this instruction is implemented.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
  </desc>
